-19T02:36:56.202Z","team_member_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2017-07-27T10:19:11.252Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"We tested the Android app, v2.0.2\n\nTo replicate:\n\n    Install the app, and run it until you reach the login screen.\n\n    Install PacketCapture:\n    https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=app.greyshirts.sslcapture\n\n    Go to PacketCapture, go through setup, SKIP the SSL certificate\n    install process\n\n    Activate PacketCapture At this point all network traffic will be\n    going through PacketCapture. SSL traffic will be encrypted using a\n    self-signed certificate, not trusted by the device.\n\n    Go back to to the app, enter any credentials and try to login.\n\n    In PacketCapture, observe login calls without any SSL being used\n\nYou can also replicate this issue with an MITM proxy\n\nImplications is that anybody monitoring the network can see the login credentials","weakness":{"id":32,"name":"Cryptographic Issues - Generic"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":null,"vote_count":2,"voters":["japz","gwedd"],"structured_scope":null,"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_groups":[]},"activities":[{"id":1182008,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugInformative","message":"Hi,\nThanks for the report. At the moment that is an accepted risk. We only have https on the checkout part of the site (most sensitive). However we have a planned change in the roadmap regarding HTTPS introduction in the customer login part.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-09-08T10:06:20.160Z","updated_at":"2016-09-08T10:06:20.160Z","actor":{"username":"aurelijus","cleared":false,"url":"/aurelijus","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/019/644/e3476b79be6c1636a8294f104b63d0f3a910bac4_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e9